71e
CERTIFICATE OF ACKNOWLEDGEMENT FOR AN INTERNATIONAL WILL
(1) The authorised person shall attach to the will a certificate of acknowledgement in which he or she shall set forth that provisions 71a to 71c of this Article have been followed.
(2) The certificate shall include:
the personal name, function and address of the person authorised to draw up an international will;
the personal name, address, date and place of birth of the testator;
the personal name, address, date and place of birth of the witnesses;
the date and place of the drawing up of the will;
confirmation that the attached will pertains to the testator and that he or she is acquainted with its content;
confirmation that the testator signed the will in the presence of the authorised person and the witnesses, or that he or she acknowledged and confirmed that the signature is his or hers (or that the testator was unable to sign the will and the reasons therefor);
confirmation that the witnesses and the authorised person have signed the will;
confirmation that each sheet of the will is signed and numbered;
confirmation of the identity of the testator and the witnesses;
confirmation that the witnesses have fulfilled the conditions specified in this Act;
a reference to the testator's statement as regards the deposit of the will;
the place, date, signature and seal.
(3) The authorised person shall keep one copy of the certificate and give another copy to the testator.
